clauses.clause:
Senior departmental managers are responsible for the following:

						Ensuring that  departmental legal  services have  been consulted  when considering  amending an existing fee or establishing a new fee;Establishing service standards for fees charged for  a service, the use of a  facility,  the  conferral of  a right or privilege,  and  a regulatory process, in accordance with relevant Treasury  Board policies and directives, including the Policy on Service and Digital and the Cabinet Directive on  Regulation; 

								Ensuring that  whether a  service standard has been met is  determined on an individual fee basis;Ensuring that fee proposals are developed and provided in full  to the Treasury Board of Canada Secretariat for review, regardless of whether or not the Service Fees Act applies, before  amending an existing fee or establishing a  new fee and before  consulting with the public. This  requirement does  not apply  to fees  that are  set by contract  or by  a method  that is  out of  the department’s  control (for  example, by  auction);
								Ensuring  that fee proposals contain: 

										A description of the activity  for which a fee is charged; Related  total costs and cost-recovery  rates, where applicable;The  proposed fee amount; The  pricing factors; The   rationale for the proposed fee; The  related service standard (if  applicable);An  impact assessment; The  expected revenue from the fee; and Other information that is deemed relevant to the department or required by the Treasury Board of Canada  Secretariat; Establishing and implementing processes for tracking and monitoring the charging of fees, compliance with service  standards, and remissions, where applicable.
